"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-hockey-paris-2024-roy-keane-team-gb-david-ames-b2584289.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  The Independent's journalism is supported by our readers.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 273, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 216, \"end\": 231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2738790975117278e-50, \"text\": \"The Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When you purchase through links on our site, we may earn commission.\", \"from\": 274, \"to\": 342, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not since the famous gold at Seoul 1988 have Great Britain's men won an Olympic hockey medal but David Ames and the Paris 2024 vintage are tapping into all resources to end that drought  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 636, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 373, \"end\": 383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9982994464102548, \"rank\": 0.0010261158902895211, \"text\": \"Seoul 1988\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 441, \"end\": 451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Ames_(actor)\", \"score\": 0.9683031453657999, \"rank\": 0.03272727272726326, \"text\": \"David Ames\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Ames_(actor)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Ames_(actor)\"}, {\"begin\": 460, \"end\": 470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6465356019296504e-18, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  It's not quite 58 years of hurt, butTeam GB's men'shockeyteam have got thefeeling that what was thencould be again.\", \"from\": 637, \"to\": 776, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 702, \"end\": 704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.830483498645788, \"rank\": 0.20411784365774774, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hockey was front page, back page, and top of the hour 36 years ago in 1988when Sean Kerly, Imran Sherwani, and keeper Ian Taylormade themselves household names at the SeoulOlympics.\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 857, \"end\": 867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sean_Kerly\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sean Kerly\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sean_Kerly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sean_Kerly\"}, {\"begin\": 869, \"end\": 883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imran_Sherwani\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imran Sherwani\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imran_Sherwani\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imran_Sherwani\"}, {\"begin\": 900, \"end\": 910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TaylorMade\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Taylormade\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TaylorMade\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TaylorMade\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They even inspired one ofBarry Davies' most famous commentaries: \\\"Where, oh where, were the Germans?\", \"from\": 961, \"to\": 1061, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1053, \"end\": 1060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.7927857760749374, \"rank\": 0.25876371062869247, \"text\": \"Germans\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And frankly, who cares?\\\"\", \"from\": 1062, \"to\": 1086, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"said the man from Auntie, losing all sense of objectivity as Sherwani scored to seal a 3-1 triumph and Olympic gold in style.\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1148, \"end\": 1156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherwani\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4868278255868863e-22, \"text\": \"Sherwani\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherwani\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherwani\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hockey came home after Seoul but Great Britain's men have had just one sniff of a medal since, losing to Australia in the bronze medal match at London 2012.By contrast, the women's teamhave made the podium at the last three Games - two bronzes sandwiching their famous penalty shootout gold in Rio.\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1512, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1237, \"end\": 1242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9995738431674299, \"rank\": 0.00035643086996775547, \"text\": \"Seoul\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1247, \"end\": 1260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999905076038, \"rank\": 6.410340701296749e-09, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_men's_national_field_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.999697066471599, \"rank\": 0.00022173610468222352, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1358, \"end\": 1369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999984452188, \"rank\": 1.5546332533114683e-09, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1508, \"end\": 1511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9997875052092341, \"rank\": 0.00021253995430481183, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But whisper it quietly, there is confidence as the men prepare to start theirParis 2024campaign against Spain at the Stade Yves-du-Manoir this weekend, the venue where Eric Liddell and Harold Abrahams' track and field exploits in 1924 inspiredChariots of Fire.\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1618, \"end\": 1623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.591805573168818e-17, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1682, \"end\": 1694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Liddell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.202856134612945e-48, \"text\": \"Eric Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Liddell\"}, {\"begin\": 1699, \"end\": 1714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_Abrahams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Harold Abrahams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_Abrahams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_Abrahams\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are ranked second in the world, behind the Netherlands, who they narrowly lost to in the final of last year's European Championships.\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 1914, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1824, \"end\": 1835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999995191798253, \"rank\": 4.783118965925472e-07, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1891, \"end\": 1913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_European_Championship\", \"score\": 0.9999999283800233, \"rank\": 7.161981533540249e-08, \"text\": \"European Championships\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_European_Championship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_European_Championship\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 16-strong men's squad features a mix of youth and experience, with seven men set to make their Olympic debuts in the French capital.\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 2052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2037, \"end\": 2043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9208064234218407, \"rank\": 0.060432199998692634, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Skipper David Ames is one of two three-time Olympians to earn selection and is seeking to follow the lead of Stephen Martin and Jimmy Kirkwood, members of the Seoul team and the last Northern Irish athletes to win Olympic gold in any sport.\", \"from\": 2053, \"to\": 2293, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2061, \"end\": 2071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Ames_(actor)\", \"score\": 0.9683031453657999, \"rank\": 0.03272727272726326, \"text\": \"David Ames\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Ames_(actor)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Ames_(actor)\"}, {\"begin\": 2170, \"end\": 2176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"score\": 0.9999981453937752, \"rank\": 1.8176548380306044e-06, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\"}, {\"begin\": 2181, \"end\": 2195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Kirkwood_(field_hockey)\", \"score\": 0.999996754062788, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jimmy Kirkwood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Kirkwood_(field_hockey)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Kirkwood_(field_hockey)\"}, {\"begin\": 2212, \"end\": 2217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9995738431674299, \"rank\": 0.00035643086996775547, \"text\": \"Seoul\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spend a few minutes in the company of the softly-spoken midfielder, and you'd never guess who his sporting inspiration was.\", \"from\": 2295, \"to\": 2418, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I tend to come out of myself when I am on a hockey pitch, but essentially, it's just trying to be the same as I always have been,\\\" explains Ames.\", \"from\": 2420, \"to\": 2566, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2561, \"end\": 2565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ames_Research_Center\", \"score\": 0.9998427001934586, \"rank\": 0.00015676921140918057, \"text\": \"Ames\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ames_Research_Center\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ames_Research_Center\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think it would be foolish for me to try to change.\", \"from\": 2567, \"to\": 2620, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Roy Keane is someone I listen to a lot.\", \"from\": 2622, \"to\": 2662, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2623, \"end\": 2632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_Keane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Roy Keane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_Keane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_Keane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has a completely different mindset to me, but he speaks very openly and very truthfully about everything.\", \"from\": 2663, \"to\": 2771, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have tried to do that myself-more than I perhaps should have.\\\"\", \"from\": 2772, \"to\": 2836, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ames credits the arrival of coach Paul Revington with instilling a new belief in the team - though do not call it 'Revsball', his players think his animated touchline manner is more J\\u00fcrgen Klopp.\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 3033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3020, \"end\": 3032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J\\u00fcrgen_Klopp\", \"score\": 0.9999999892861525, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"J\\u00fcrgen Klopp\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J\\u00fcrgen_Klopp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J\\u00fcrgen_Klopp\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Revington is a former world coach of the year, taking his native South Africa to the Olympics in 2004 before spells with Ireland, Great Britain, where he coached the women's team, and Malaysia.\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3228, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3100, \"end\": 3112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9343694060090297, \"rank\": 0.07001394813046952, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3156, \"end\": 3163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9940744001498457, \"rank\": 0.00319901925345828, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3165, \"end\": 3178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999905076038, \"rank\": 6.410340701296749e-09, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_men's_national_field_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3219, \"end\": 3227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.996288357326558, \"rank\": 0.00368268053020139, \"text\": \"Malaysia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He's brought in a fast-paced style of hockey and instilled in us a desire to do whatever it takes to stand on podiums,\\\" adds Ames.\", \"from\": 3230, \"to\": 3361, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3356, \"end\": 3360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ames_Research_Center\", \"score\": 0.9998427001934586, \"rank\": 0.00015676921140918057, \"text\": \"Ames\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ames_Research_Center\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ames_Research_Center\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's pretty much all we ever speak about.\\\"\", \"from\": 3362, \"to\": 3407, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Revington's squad talk a lot about the confidence he has instilled and his relentless focus on winning.\", \"from\": 3409, \"to\": 3512, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Revs has done incredible things for a lot of guys' belief,\\\" said Phil Roper, who is making his second Olympic appearance in Paris.\", \"from\": 3514, \"to\": 3645, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3580, \"end\": 3590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Roper\", \"score\": 0.9999919308677775, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Phil Roper\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Roper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Roper\"}, {\"begin\": 3639, \"end\": 3644, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.6969725949202706e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He wants us to play an exciting brand of hockey and that's what we want to do - to play in a way that fans can get behind and people enjoy watching.\", \"from\": 3647, \"to\": 3796, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thankfully, I am probably one of those players who has benefited because I like having the freedom to go and try things, to score great goals and make nice actions.\\\"\", \"from\": 3797, \"to\": 3962, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Richard Dodds, who captained Great Britain to gold in Seoul, was drafted in by Revington to speak to the team before they flew out to France.\", \"from\": 3964, \"to\": 4105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3964, \"end\": 3977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Dodds\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Richard Dodds\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Dodds\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Dodds\"}, {\"begin\": 3993, \"end\": 4006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999905076038, \"rank\": 6.410340701296749e-09, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_men's_national_field_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_men's_national_field_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4018, \"end\": 4023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9995738431674299, \"rank\": 0.00035643086996775547, \"text\": \"Seoul\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 4098, \"end\": 4104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9925153740452095, \"rank\": 0.007541068027736532, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dodds, who became an orthopaedic surgeon, was the classic thinking captain, capable of going full Churchill in his inspirational team talks.\", \"from\": 4106, \"to\": 4246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4204, \"end\": 4213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Winston_Churchill\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7665153366196523e-16, \"text\": \"Churchill\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Winston_Churchill\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Winston_Churchill\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His vice-captain, Paul Barber, preferred to instil fear, unleashing a few strongly worded home truths before their semi-final against Australia.\", \"from\": 4248, \"to\": 4392, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4266, \"end\": 4277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Barber_(actor)\", \"score\": 0.86448271661316, \"rank\": 0.13860887096770658, \"text\": \"Paul Barber\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Barber_(actor)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Barber_(actor)\"}, {\"begin\": 4382, \"end\": 4391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.999697066471599, \"rank\": 0.00022173610468222352, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Everyone thinks you are good, but I am not so sure,\\\" he famously told Kerly, who'd scored four goals in five games to earn comparisons with Gary Lineker.\", \"from\": 4394, \"to\": 4548, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4535, \"end\": 4547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gary_Lineker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gary Lineker\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gary_Lineker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gary_Lineker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's time you went out and proved it.\\\"\", \"from\": 4549, \"to\": 4588, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kerly duly netted a hat-trick in a 3-2 win over the gold medal favourites.\", \"from\": 4590, \"to\": 4664, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We watched a video of 1988, and it got us all so excited,\\\" said Jacob Draper.\", \"from\": 4666, \"to\": 4744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4731, \"end\": 4743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacob_Draper\", \"score\": 0.9999732867184433, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jacob Draper\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacob_Draper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacob_Draper\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It probably came a little early because we left the meeting thinking 'can we play some more'?\", \"from\": 4745, \"to\": 4839, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was a video of the Seoul 1988 team when they won gold.\", \"from\": 4841, \"to\": 4899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4864, \"end\": 4874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9982994464102548, \"rank\": 0.0010261158902895211, \"text\": \"Seoul 1988\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was their route to it, the semi-final against Australia, the final against Germany, and watching a team from Great Britain do what they did is incredibly special.\", \"from\": 4900, \"to\": 5065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4949, \"end\": 4958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.999697066471599, \"rank\": 0.00022173610468222352, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4978, \"end\": 4985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_t